The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Tuesday, October 18, 2005 

 BRIEFS

 Burdwan, Oct. 17: Ajmira Khatun, a Class X student who fled home unable to bear her step-mothers torture and refusal to let her study, was today found on the Burdwan Medical College and Hospital premises.

 The deputy superintendent of the hospital spotted the 15-year-old from Memari, 90 km from Calcutta, sitting on a staircase. The student of Bijpur AB High School was preparing for her exams on Sunday when her mother beat her up and told her to abandon studies and do household chores. Police would escort Ajmira home.

 Durgapur: The foundation stone for a second line dedicated to goods trains was laid at Durgapur station on Monday. The Rs 3-crore project, to be completed within 2006, will speed up unloading of goods from wagons, Eastern Railway general manager Shyam Kumar said.




